This document is an "IBM Batch Report" PDF, dated June 15, 2016, detailing the processing of 50 ballots within Batch Number 22 from the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) for Electoral Event ID 19694 in NSW. It provides batch metadata and a comprehensive breakdown of automated and manual checks for each ballot, including Quality Assurance, Initials, Official Mark, Unusual Markings, Formality Result, Verification Action, Formality Reason, and Above-the-Line (ATL) and Below-the-Line (BTL) preference processing status. While most checks show "OK" for successful processing, two ballots (Ballot 26 and Ballot 37) are flagged with "HAS ISSUES" under 'UnusualMarkings Checked', accompanied by specific codes `['E1 ']` and `['A1 ']` respectively.

This document is highly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] as it is a direct example of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files sought from 'IBM Outputs' in 2016. It provides the detailed ballot-level insights, batch metadata, and electoral event context specified in the request overview. Crucially, it demonstrates the presence of "HAS ISSUES" entries for ballot checks, such as `UnusualMarkings Checked` with accompanying alphanumeric codes (`E1`, `A1`), which is a primary focus area of the FOI request regarding anomalies and exceptions in the ballot processing.

Do not include any conversational filler or preamble.To aid you, the overview of the FOI request is: [REQUEST OVERVIEW START] Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] sought documents related to 'IBM Outputs' from 2016, yielding 106 "IBM Batch Report" PDF files dated June 8, 10, and 15, 2016, categorized by Vote Collection Point and Batch Number. These detailed reports provide insights into ballot processing, including batch metadata, electoral event context, and specific ballot-level checks for formality, initials, marks, and preferences (ATL/BTL). While most entries indicate "OK" for successful processing, various checks, notably `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches`, frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries, often accompanied by alphanumeric codes (e.g., D2, Y9, M1, U1), signifying specific anomalies or exceptions in the ballot processing.
